actions.comment:
Thanks for the report and the comparison images.

@gnattu's analysis is correct — the old `SKFilterQuality.High` was direction-dependent: cubic (Mitchell) for upscaling, bilinear+mipmaps for downscaling. The `ToSamplingOptions()` compatibility shim maps `High` unconditionally to `SKCubicResampler.Mitchell`, which isn't optimal for downscaling.

Here's a workaround you can use now:

```csharp
bool isDownscaling = bitmapDst.Width < bitmapSrc.Width || bitmapDst.Height < bitmapSrc.Height;
var sampling = isDownscaling
    ? new SKSamplingOptions(SKFilterMode.Linear, SKMipmapMode.Linear)
    : new SKSamplingOptions(SKCubicResampler.Mitchell);
bitmapSrc.ScalePixels(bitmapDst, sampling);
```

We'll look into improving the migration guidance and the compatibility layer to make this less of a gotcha.
